91/2.text_en:
Section 91/2. The following businesses carried on in Thailand shall be subject to specific business tax:
(1) Banking;
(2) Finance, securities, and credit foncier business;
(3) Life insurance;
(4) Pawnbroking;
(5) Business with regular transactions similar to commercial banks;
(6) Sale of immovable property in a commercial manner or for profit.
For the purposes of (6), 'sale of immovable property in a commercial manner or for profit' means a sale by any person who is not a developer, which includes an immovable property acquired and sold within five years from the date of acquisition, as prescribed by the Royal Decree.
